[Look Ahead 4.21.21.xlsx](https://github.com/exceljs/exceljs/files/6381608/Look.Ahead.4.21.21.xlsx)
## 🐛 Bug Report

<!-- A clear and concise description of what the bug is. -->
When parsing the attached xlsx file with background fill color in some of the cells the style object does not return the correct information.

Lib version: 4.2.1

## Steps To Reproduce

<!-- The exact steps required to reproduce the issue, ideally with a code example -->
parse the attached file and see that cell AO48 for example returns the following fill object under the cell.style.fill:
{
  bgColor: {indexed: 64}
  fgColor: {theme: 4, tint: -0.249977111117893}
  pattern: "solid"
  type: "pattern"
}

where as cell AO19 returns the correct value as:
{
  bgColor: {indexed: 64}
  fgColor: {argb: "FF92D050"}
  pattern: "solid"
  type: "pattern"
}

```javascript
var cell = sheet.getCell('AO48');
console.log(cell.style.fill);

cell = sheet.getCell('AO19');
console.log(cell.style.fill);
```

## The expected behaviour:

<!-- A clear and concise description of what you expected to happen. -->
I expect that the cell will have a fill object that contains the `argb` key with a value instead of `theme` and `tint`


