@ryanmee-ix , @KaivnD , @ZoharLiran 

Read `workbook._themes.theme1` and parse the XML. FG Colour `theme` correlates to each `<a:accent#index#>` in the theme XML. If you are only wanting accent colours, then subtract 3 from the `theme` value and it will line up with the accents.

Tint is a percentage of lightness or darkness. You can use the function found here: [programmatically-lighten-or-darken-a-hex-color-or-rgb-and-blend-colors](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/5560248/programmatically-lighten-or-darken-a-hex-color-or-rgb-and-blend-colors) , multiply tint by 100 and pass that as the amount to lighten (0.41 * 100 becomes 41%).
